## PHASE 0 — Anatomy extraction (inventory the source before you touch anything)

The source has no standard structure, so first find each part and write down where
it lives. Produce this inventory (in your head or as a scratch comment), mapping each
to its shell home (see `SHELL-DESIGN-GUIDE.md` §2):

| Find in the source                                            | Shell home |
|---------------------------------------------------------------|------------|
| Page title / `<h1>` / `<title>` + any subtitle                | `.shell-title` (subtitle in a `<span>`) |
| The render surface (`<canvas>`, `<svg>`, p5 canvas, three.js `<div>`) | `.shell-hero` → wrapped in `.plot-box` |
| The animation loop (`requestAnimationFrame`, p5 `draw()`, three render loop, `setInterval`) | rewired to `onFrame(dt)` (Phase 3) |
| Play / Pause / Stop / Reset / Restart buttons                 | **Delete** → shell's `#shell-play` / `#shell-reset` |
| Speed / time-scale control                                    | **Delete** → shell's `#shell-speed` |
| "Show equations / formal" checkbox                            | **Delete** → shell's `∑ Formal` (`#toggle-formal`) |
| Parameter sliders (v, β, mass, angle…)                        | `#aside-controls` → `.ctrl-box--slider` |
| View toggles / mode switches (grid, frame, layer…)            | `#aside-controls` → `.ctrl-box` + `.stat-row` |
| Readouts / stat panels / live numbers                         | `#aside-controls` → `.ctrl-box` with `.stat-row`s |
| Any prediction / quiz / "guess first" block                   | Guided-inquiry **step cards** in `#inq-cards` (Phase 5) |
| Equations / MathJax / KaTeX / formulae                        | `.shell-formal` (Phase 6) |
| External libs (`<script src=…p5/three/d3…>`)                  | **Keep** — copy the `<script>`/`<link>` tags into `<head>` |
| Physics + drawing JS                                          | **Keep verbatim** in the SIM section; only the loop is rewired |

Note the **framework** (vanilla canvas / p5 / three / SVG / DOM) — it changes only
how you rewire the loop in Phase 3.

---

## PHASE 1 — Scaffold the global skeleton (self-contained)

Rebuild the document around the extracted parts using the skeleton from
`SHELL-DESIGN-GUIDE.md` §3 / `reference-converted-sim.html`. Fill only the marked
regions; **never rename a shell class or ID** — the runtime wires them by name.

1. **Head.** Keep `<meta charset>` + viewport. Keep the KaTeX `<link>` +
   `<script defer>` (add them if the sim needs equations). Keep any source library
   `<script src>` tags. Then make the file **self-contained** (scraped sims travel
   without their assets):
   - Inline the full contents of `_design-reference/simulation-shell.css` into a
     `<style>` in `<head>` (do not edit it), **and** copy the
     `<style data-sim-fonts>@font-face{…base64…}</style>` block verbatim from
     `reference-converted-sim.html` so the fonts embed.
   - Put only small, sim-specific CSS in a second `<style>` (canvas cursor, the
     `.formal-grid`, the `.inq-step`/`.predict-eval` rules from §6, etc.). Convert
     the source's own layout CSS to design **tokens** (`var(--bg)`, `var(--surface)`,
     `var(--text)`, `var(--accent)`, `var(--border)`…) or drop it if the shell
     already styles that region. Do NOT restyle the render surface's internals.
2. **Body root.** Wrap everything in `<div id="shell" class="hide-formal">` (the
   `hide-formal` class keeps the formal region hidden until the student opts in).
3. **Regions, in order:** the `#shell-info-modal`, then `<header class="shell-header">`
   (global controls only — canonical order: title · `#shell-info` · `#shell-theme` ·
   `#shell-maximize` · `#toggle-formal` · Speed `#shell-speed` · `#shell-reset` ·
   `#shell-play`), then `<main class="shell-hero">`, then `<aside class="shell-aside">`
   (the two-zone sidebar), then `<section class="shell-formal">`. Copy each wrapper
   verbatim from the reference. Drop `∑ Formal` only if there is no formal region;
   drop Speed **and** Play only if there is genuinely nothing to animate (see the
   static-slider note in Physics honesty).
4. **Hero.** Move the render surface into `.shell-hero`, wrapped in
   `<div class="plot-box">` (optional `.plot-title` / `.legend`). **Do not change the
   canvas/svg element's id, width/height attributes, or the draw code.**

