## Theming, tokens & physics honesty (do not skip)

- **Use tokens, not hex,** for all chrome and SIM CSS so both themes work. For canvas
  colours, read the token once (`getComputedStyle(document.documentElement)
  .getPropertyValue('--accent')`) and re-read in `onResize`/redraw so a theme switch
  recolours the canvas. Keep the SR frame colours `--rest` / `--moving` / `--photon`
  constant across themes. The cream top bar is theme-independent — leave it.
- **Physics honesty (§11) — keep the science truthful during re-housing:**
  - **Never auto-sweep a velocity / β / v/c over time** — that implies an
    accelerating frame. Expose velocity as a **static slider**; the scene updates on
    drag. If the source auto-ramped v/c, convert it to a slider unless the sim's whole
    point is genuine acceleration.
  - **A function plot is not a particle** — tie any marker to the slider value, don't
    animate a dot along a curve.
  - **No proper-time clock on a photon** (dτ = 0 on a null worldline).
  - **Re-describing ≠ moving:** when a control changes the reference *frame*, relabel
    axes (S→S′) and redraw the grid.
  - **Interval sign convention:** `ds² = (cΔt)² − (Δx)²` (timelike > 0, spacelike < 0,
    lightlike 0), used consistently.
  - Canvas labels ≥ 12px, prose ≥ 14px; on-canvas text is labels only.
  - These are honesty rules about presentation — they must NOT alter the source's
    physics math. If applying one would change the physics, leave it and flag it.

